## Before your electrician arrives

A few steps make the visit safer and faster:

- Note which rooms or circuits are affected and when the problem started.
- Keep children and pets away from open boards or exposed wiring until the visit.
- Clear access to the switchboard, affected sockets, and the work area.
- Share if you have an inverter or generator so the partner can plan around backup power.
- Be home, or have someone available to show the fault and approve the work.

If you smell burning, see sparks, or the board keeps tripping, treat it as urgent — call us and avoid resetting breakers repeatedly until a professional checks the circuit.

